Sent on behalf of Tony Bailetti, TIM Academic Director

Dear TIM students,

Good afternoon! We are excited to share two important files with you today:

  1.  PPTX Slide Deck =96 =93AI-First in the Technology Innovation Manageme=
nt (TIM) Program)=94
This deck outlines the baseline expectations for AI use in the TIM program.=
 From now on, AI will be considered a core skill =97 integrated into everyt=
hing we do as students, faculty, and staff. These expectations take effect =
immediately. Our goal is to prepare TM students to become leaders in techno=
logy innovation for a world where AI is everywhere.
  2.  DOCX Document =96 =93AI-First@TIM=94
This summer, we=92re launching AI-First@TIM =97 a bold new initiative that =
puts AI at the heart of how we learn, create, and solve real-world challeng=
es. It=92s your chance to build cutting-edge skills, explore the latest AI =
tools, and stand out in a fast-moving tech landscape.
By joining one of the three AI-First@TIM learning paths, you can:

  *   Earn a Certificate of Completion from the TIM program
  *   Gain hands-on, AI-first experience aligned with your career goals
  *   Collaborate with mentors, faculty, and industry professionals
  *   Learn how to apply AI ethically, effectively, and creatively
To apply to participate in one of the three paths of AI-First this summer, =
please send a cv to Dan Premachuk (dan.premachuk@carleton.ca<mailto:dan.pre=
machuk@carleton.ca>) and a paragraph that describes the project and path th=
at which you wish to be a part before 11:59 PM Friday June 6, 2025. If you =
apply to path 3 AI-First@TIM: Accelerator, please describe the type of comp=
anies with which you wish to engage.

If you have any questions or need more information, please reach out to Dan=
 Premachuk, TIM Administrator.

Looking forward to examining what you accomplish by the end of this summer =
term!

Warm regards,
Tony Bailetti, Ph.D.
Academic Director, TIM Program


